  "active_lock_reason": "resolved",
  "body": "In hardhat.config.ts I cannot specify the etherscan `apiKey` parameter as an object, thus I'm unable to use one config for multiple evms.\r\n\r\n```\r\nhardhat.config.ts:78:5 - error TS2322: Type '{ mainnet: string | undefined; rinkeby: string | undefined; polygon: string | undefined; polygonMumbai: string | undefined; bsc: string | undefined; bscTestnet: string | undefined; }' is not assignable to type 'string'\r\n```\r\n\r\nExcerpt from config:\r\n\r\n```\r\n  etherscan: {\r\n    apiKey: {\r\n      mainnet: process.env.ETHERSCAN_API_KEY,\r\n      rinkeby: process.env.ETHERSCAN_API_KEY,\r\n      polygon: process.env.POLYGONSCAN_API_KEY,\r\n      polygonMumbai: process.env.POLYGONSCAN_API_KEY,\r\n      bsc: process.env.BSCSCAN_API_KEY,\r\n      bscTestnet: process.env.BSCSCAN_API_KEY,\r\n    }\r\n  }\r\n```\r\n\r\nMy current workaround is to just manually swap in and out keys depending on the chain I'm aiming for:\r\n```\r\n  etherscan: {\r\n    //apiKey: process.env.ETHERSCAN_API_KEY\r\n    apiKey: process.env.POLYGONSCAN_API_KEY\r\n    //apiKey: process.env.BSCSCAN_API_KEY\r\n  },\r\n```",
